
                        Section 2 - Notes
                         ENV Instruction

1.  Dockerfile in this directory.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    # Dockerfile for ENV instruction
    FROM ubuntu
    ENV TOPDIR /usr/bob
    ENV CUSTOMER1="mysql" CUSTOMER2="hadoop"
    CMD ["/bin/bash"]

2.  Build image.

    $ docker build -t env . 

3.  Enter container and show environment variables.

    $ docker run -it env
    root@1878cbd67073:/# echo $TOPDIR
    /usr/bob
    root@1878cbd67073:/# echo $CUSTOMER1 $CUSTOMER2
    mysql hadoop
    root@1878cbd67073:/# exit 

